      "instructions": "Thaw 2 boxes frozen chopped spinach and 1 box of frozen artichoke.  I remove them from the freezer and put them in the fridge overnight.Preheat oven to 400 degreesSqueeze out all the moisture from the spinach.  I like to make it completely dryChop the artichoke hearts to smaller piecesIn a medium pan, add 2 Tbsp of extra virgin olive oil and set the heat to highAdd 1/4 cup of finely chopped red onionsLet the onions caramelize for a few minutes and then add 2 cubes of Dorot Crushed GarlicThe garlic will melt almost immediately.  Add the chopped artichoke and let them caramelize.  Should take about 15 minutesAdd the thawed spinachAdd 2 cubes of Dorot Chopped Basil and mix wellAdd 1.5 cups of milk (or light cream).  Add 2 tsp of sea salt and 1 tsp of lime juiceSet the heat to medium and let it simmer for about 15 minutesTransfer half of the contents to an oven safe pan.  I like cast iron for this recipeAdd 1/2 cup of shredded mozzarella cheese then top it off with the rest of the hot spinach dipFinally top it with 3/4 cup of shredded mozzarella and place it in the oven for about 15 minutes or until the top turns brown",
