      "instructions": "1. Heat broiler. On a foil-lined baking sheet, broil the poblano, turning occasionally, until blistered all over, 4 to 6 minutes. Transfer to a small bowl and cover with plastic wrap to let the steam loosen the skin.2. When the poblano is cool, peel, seed and finely dice it. Set aside.3. Using a paring knife, score through the avocado flesh, creating a grid-like pattern. Scoop out the avocado flesh into a medium bowl and toss with lime juice. Add the onion, cilantro, tomato, olive oil, cumin and season with salt and pepper. Add the pecans and the poblano and lightly mash using the tines of a fork. Serve immediately.",
