        "pairingText": "Lamb Shanks works really well with Cabernet Sauvignon, Malbec, and Shiraz. Red wine with red meat is fairly standard, but these bold reds with smoother tannins complement lamb's delicate flavor. One wine you could try is Sean Minor Napa Valley Cabernet Sauvignon. It has 4.4 out of 5 stars and a bottle costs about 18 dollars.",
