        "pairingText": "Mexican works really well with Pinot Noir, Riesling, and Sparkling rosé. Acidic white wines like riesling or low-tannin reds like pinot noir can work well with Mexican dishes. Sparkling rosé is a safe pairing too. One wine you could try is Roco Gravel Road Pinot Noir. It has 4.1 out of 5 stars and a bottle costs about 26 dollars.",
